column1: # Data from Yurtsev et al (2013) Mol Syst Biol 9:683, Figs. 1, 3
# Data authors: Eugene A Yurtsev, Hui Xiao Chao, Manoshi S Datta, Tatiana Artemova, Jeff Gore
# resistant = Escherichia coli expressing expressing TEM-1 beta-lactamase, resistant to ampicillin
# sensitive = Escherichia coli wild type, sensitive to ampicillin
# antibiotic = initial concentration of ampicillin in culture media (micrograms/ml)
# dilution = fold dilution to set initial population density (part of experimental treatment)
# culture.id = culture identification number within replicate
# initial.proportion.A = initial proportion of resistant cells, determined by flow cytometry
# final.proportion.A = final proportion of resistant cells, determined by flow cytometry
